; drums_808.mml
; -------------------------------------------------------------------
; TR-808 style drum patterns for an open-source, text-based groovebox.
; This file is intended as a seed for Copilot to extend.
;
; Mapping concept (engine-dependent – adapt to your MML driver):
;   C = 808 kick
;   D = 808 snare
;   E = 808 low tom
;   F = 808 mid tom
;   G = 808 hi tom / rim
;   A = closed hat
;   B = open hat / clap
;
; Groove: 4/4, 125 BPM, house / electro with 80s flavour.

t125          ; tempo
l16           ; default note length = 16th notes
o4            ; base octave for drum mapping
v14           ; main drum volume

; -------------------------------------------------------------------
; PATTERN: DRUM_MAIN_A
; Classic four-on-the-floor 808 pattern (4 bars)
; Kick on every beat, snare on 2 + 4, hats on 8ths.
; Use as "MC-303 style" main groove.

; Bar 1–4:
;  Beat:   1   &   2   &   3   &   4   &
;  Kick:   C               C
;  Snare:          D               D
;  Hats:   A   A   A   A   A   A   A   A

; CHANNEL: drums main
; (Some MML engines expect channel prefixes like "A", "B" etc.)

; @808_KIT  ; uncomment / adapt if your engine supports drum kits

[
  ; bar 1
  C--- A-A- D--- A-A- C--- A-A- D--- A-A-
  ; bar 2 (add off-beat clap / open hat flavour)
  C--- A-B- D--- A-A- C--- A-B- D--- A-A-
  ; bar 3 (slight variation on hats)
  C--- A-A- D-A- A-A- C--- A-A- D-A- A-A-
  ; bar 4 (little fill with toms)
  C--- A-A- D--- A-A- C--- A-A- D-EF A-B-
]2           ; repeat this 4-bar phrase twice

; -------------------------------------------------------------------
; PATTERN: DRUM_BREAK_A
; Simple breakdown: keep hats, drop most kicks, tease snare.
; Good for 80s-style build ups.

; bar 1–2: hats with sparse kicks
[
  ; bar 1
  C--- A-A- ---- A-A- ---- A-A- ---- A-A-
  ; bar 2 (snare teaser)
  ---- A-A- D--- A-A- ---- A-A- D--- A-A-
]2

; -------------------------------------------------------------------
; GAME SFX + FUNNY / NOSTALGIC HITS (drum-voice stubs)
; These can be mapped to extra samples in your engine:
;   High-pitched tom / rim = retro "UI blip" / "coin" sound
;   Very short noise burst = "8-bit explosion" or "funny pop"

; Example: 1-bar "coin pickup" fill at the end of a section.
; Treat G as "coin" sample, B as "cartoon pop" sample.

; COIN_FILL_A
; place on a separate channel or at the end of DRUM_MAIN_A loop

; v12          ; slightly lower volume for SFX layer
; o5           ; higher octave mapping if your engine uses pitch

; 16th-note run into the downbeat:
; GGGG GGGG GGGG B---   ; coins → cartoon pop on beat 4

; -------------------------------------------------------------------
; TODO / HINTS FOR COPILOT
; - Generate additional patterns:
;   - DRUM_MAIN_B: electro / early hip-hop, sparser kicks, more claps.
;   - DRUM_FILL_A/B: 1-bar and 2-bar tom runs in 808 style.
;   - DRUM_GAME_A: 8-bit-influenced hats (alternating A / G) for
;     "open-source retro game" levels.
; - Comment patterns clearly so they can be chained by a groovebox-style
;   engine (A, B, BREAK, FILL, etc).
